<Layout
	title="Privacy Policy"
	description="How Apex Engine collects, uses, and protects your information, in line with the Philippine Data Privacy Act of 2012."
>
	<p><em>Last updated: 16 July 2026</em></p>

	<p>
		This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Apex Engine</strong> ("we", "us", or "our") collects,
		uses, and protects information when you visit <strong>apexenginehq.com</strong> (the "Site").
		We are committed to handling your personal data responsibly and in accordance with the
		<strong>Data Privacy Act of 2012 (Republic Act No. 10173)</strong> of the Philippines and the
		issuances of the National Privacy Commission (NPC). By using the Site, you agree to the practices
		described here.
	</p>

	<h2>Information We Collect</h2>
	<h3>Information you provide</h3>
	<p>
		When you contact us — for example, through our contact form or by email — we collect the details
		you choose to share, such as your name, email address, and the contents of your message. We use
		this only to respond to and manage your inquiry.
	</p>
	<h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
	<p>
		Like most websites, we automatically collect limited technical information when you browse the
		Site, including your device and browser type, approximate location, pages viewed, referring
		pages, and (in aggregated or shortened form) your IP address. This is gathered through analytics
		and standard server logs to help us understand how the Site is used and to keep it secure.
	</p>
	<h3>Cookies and similar technologies</h3>
	<p>
		We use cookies and similar technologies for analytics and advertising. Cookies are small files stored
		on your device. Some cookies are set by third parties, including our advertising partner (see
			"Advertising" below). You can refuse or delete cookies through your browser settings; doing so will not
		break the Site, though some features may behave differently.
	</p>

	<h2>Analytics</h2>
	<p>
		We use <strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> to understand aggregate visitor behavior (for example,
		which guides are most read). Google Analytics sets cookies and processes usage data on our behalf.
		Our analytics is configured to run only on our live domain. You can opt out of Google Analytics
		across all sites by installing the
		<a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google
		Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>. For more information, see
		<a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google's
		Privacy Policy</a>.
	</p>

	<h2>Advertising</h2>
		<p>
			We display ads through <strong>Google AdSense</strong>, an advertising service provided by Google.
			To serve ads, Google and its partners use cookies and similar technologies — including the
			<strong>Google advertising cookie (DART cookie)</strong> — to serve ads based on your prior visits
			to this Site and other sites on the internet. Third-party vendors, including Google, may collect
			or receive information such as your device data, approximate location, and browsing activity to
			measure and personalize the ads you see.
		</p>
		<p>
			You can opt out of personalized advertising by visiting
			<a href="https://adssettings.google.com" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google Ads
			Settings</a>, and you can manage third-party ad-serving cookies at
			<a href="https://optout.aboutads.info" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">aboutads.info</a>
			and <a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.com" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Your Online
			Choices</a>. For details on how Google uses information from sites that use its services, see
			<a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google's
			partner-sites policy</a>. Any future affiliate links on the Site are disclosed on the pages where
			they appear.
		</p>

		<h2>How We Use Information</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>To operate, maintain, and improve the Site and its content.</li>
		<li>To respond to your messages, questions, and requests.</li>
		<li>To analyze usage trends and measure the performance of our content.</li>
		<li>To protect the Site against fraud, abuse, and security threats.</li>
		<li>To comply with legal obligations.</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		Our lawful bases for processing include your <strong>consent</strong> (which you may withdraw at
		any time), our <strong>legitimate interests</strong> in running and improving the Site, and
		<strong>compliance with law</strong>.
	</p>

	<h2>Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
	<p>
		<strong>We do not sell your personal data.</strong> We share information only with trusted service
		providers who help us run the Site — currently our hosting provider (Vercel) and our analytics
		provider (Google Analytics), and our advertising provider (Google AdSense) — and only as needed for those services. We may also disclose information when
		required by law, court order, or a lawful request from a public authority, or to protect our
		rights, users, and the public. Some of these providers may process data outside the Philippines;
		where this happens, we take reasonable steps to ensure appropriate protection.
	</p>

	<h2>Data Retention</h2>
	<p>
		We keep personal data only for as long as necessary for the purposes described above, to comply
		with legal obligations, or to resolve disputes. Inquiry-related messages are retained for a
		reasonable period and then deleted or anonymized.
	</p>

	<h2>Data Security</h2>
	<p>
		We apply reasonable organizational and technical measures to protect personal data against
		unauthorized access, loss, or misuse. However, no method of transmission or storage is completely
		secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
	</p>

	<h2>Your Rights</h2>
	<p>
		Under the Data Privacy Act of 2012, you have the right to be informed, and to access, correct,
		object to the processing of, suspend, or request the erasure of your personal data, as well as the
		right to data portability and to lodge a complaint with the National Privacy Commission. To
		exercise any of these rights, contact us at the email below.
	</p>

	<h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
	<p>
		The Site is intended for a general adult audience and is not directed at children under 18. We do
		not knowingly collect personal data from minors. If you believe a minor has provided us
		information, please contact us so we can remove it.
	</p>

	<h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
	<p>
		The Site may link to third-party websites (such as manufacturers, dealerships, and reference
		sources). We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of those sites. We encourage
		you to review their policies before sharing personal information.
	</p>

	<h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
	<p>
		We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes take effect when posted, and the
		"Last updated" date above will reflect the latest revision. Significant changes will be made
		reasonably prominent.
	</p>

	<h2>Contact Us</h2>
	<p>
		For privacy questions or to exercise your rights, contact us at
		<a href="mailto:info@apexenginehq.com">info@apexenginehq.com</a>. You may also contact the
		National Privacy Commission (<a href="https://privacy.gov.ph" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">privacy.gov.ph</a>)
		if you believe your data privacy rights have been violated.
	</p>
</Layout>
